Phase 2 — SDD Workflow & Required Artifacts

Based on the approved SSOT, the following implementation artifacts were derived before final code development. These artifacts define the structure of the application and the verification approach for the pricing logic.
2.1 Artifact 1 — Implementation Plan
2.1.1 Development Objective
The purpose of the implementation plan is to translate the SSOT into a working Angular single-page application that calculates monthly cloud costs for a chatbot system and can be deployed through Firebase Hosting.
2.1.2 Application Structure

The application is organized into the following logical components:
ChatShellComponent — main layout container for the calculator interface
InputFormComponent — collects all usage assumptions from the user
ResultsPanelComponent — displays the cost breakdown and total monthly cost
PricingEngineService — implements all pricing formulas defined in the SSOT
Validation Layer — ensures all user inputs satisfy the rules defined in the specification

2.1.3 Component Responsibilities
ChatShellComponent
Acts as the main page container. It arranges the header, calculator form, and results panel.
InputFormComponent
Contains the full calculator form. It captures all required parameters:
Monthly Users
Messages per User per Month
Average Input Tokens per Message
Average Output Tokens per Message
Monthly Function Invocations
Execution Time per Invocation
Memory Allocation
Database Storage
Monthly Document Writes
Cloud Storage Usage
Gemini model selection
ResultsPanelComponent
Receives the calculated results and displays:
Compute Cost
LLM Inference Cost
Firestore Cost
Cloud Storage Cost
Total Monthly Cost
PricingEngineService
Implements all mathematical formulas from the SSOT as pure calculation functions. This service must not contain UI logic.

2.1.4 Calculation Workflow
The application must follow this sequence:
The user enters usage data in the input form.
The validation layer checks whether all required values are valid.
If validation passes, the input values are passed to the PricingEngineService.
The PricingEngineService computes all intermediate metrics and cost components.
The total monthly cost is calculated.
The ResultsPanelComponent displays the final breakdown.

2.1.5 Formula Mapping
Compute Cost
Convert execution time from milliseconds to seconds
Compute GB-seconds
Compute invocation cost
Compute runtime cost
Sum both values
LLM Cost
Compute total messages
Compute total input tokens
Compute total output tokens
Select Gemini pricing tier
Compute input token cost
Compute output token cost
Sum both values
Firestore Cost
Compute storage cost
Compute write operations cost
Sum both values
Cloud Storage Cost
Multiply storage usage by fixed monthly GB rate
Total Monthly Cost
Sum Compute, LLM, Firestore, and Cloud Storage costs

