2.1.7 UI Plan
The user interface must include:
a header section with project title and description
a structured calculator form
a calculate button
a results dashboard showing each cost component
a visually emphasized total monthly cost
The layout should be responsive and suitable for desktop presentation.

2.1.8 Deployment Plan
After local testing, the application will be built using Angular production build tools and deployed via Firebase Hosting.
Deployment steps:
Build the Angular application
Configure Firebase Hosting
Set the Angular build output directory as the hosting public directory
Deploy the application
Verify that the public Firebase URL is accessible and working

2.2 Artifact 2 — Test Specification Suite
The purpose of the test specification suite is to verify that every pricing formula defined in the SSOT is implemented correctly and produces deterministic results.

2.2.1 Validation Tests

Test V1 — Reject Negative Values
Input contains one or more negative numeric values.
Expected result: calculation is blocked and a validation error is shown.

Test V2 — Reject Memory Below 128 MB
Memory allocation is below 128 MB.
Expected result: calculation is blocked and a validation error is shown.

Test V3 — Reject Empty Required Fields
One or more required inputs are missing.
Expected result: calculation is blocked and the user is prompted to complete the form.

2.2.2 Formula Tests
Test Case 1 — Normal Usage / Gemini Flash

Inputs
Monthly Users = 1000
Messages per User per Month = 20
Avg Input Tokens per Message = 150
Avg Output Tokens per Message = 300
Monthly Function Invocations = 20000
Execution Time per Invocation = 500 ms
Memory Allocation = 256 MB
Database Storage = 5 GB
Monthly Document Writes = 50000
Cloud Storage Usage = 10 GB
Model = Gemini 1.5 Flash
Expected Calculation
TotalMessages = 1000 × 20 = 20000
TotalInputTokens = 20000 × 150 = 3,000,000
TotalOutputTokens = 20000 × 300 = 6,000,000
LLM Input Cost = 3,000,000 / 1,000,000 × 0.075 = 0.225
LLM Output Cost = 6,000,000 / 1,000,000 × 0.30 = 1.80
LLM Cost = 2.025
ExecutionTimeSeconds = 500 / 1000 = 0.5
GBSeconds = (256 / 1024) × 0.5 × 20000 = 2500
Invocation Cost = 20000 / 1,000,000 × 0.40 = 0.008
Runtime Cost = 2500 × 0.0000025 = 0.00625
Compute Cost = 0.01425
Firestore Storage Cost = 5 × 0.18 = 0.90
Firestore Write Cost = 50000 / 100000 × 0.06 = 0.03
Firestore Cost = 0.93
Cloud Storage Cost = 10 × 0.02 = 0.20
Expected TotalMonthlyCost
0.01425 + 2.025 + 0.93 + 0.20 = 3.16925 USD
Expected displayed total: $3.17
